\h ZOOM \d

\uUSAGE\n
!zoom \s[\dlevel\s]\d

\uDESCRIPTION\n
Set the zoom level of the Mudlet mapper.
A zoom level of 1 represents the greatest possible degree of magnification. The greater the zoom level, the more the map will zoom out.
When no arguments are provided, the zoom will be set to the default level of @o.

\uEXAMPLES\n
\qzoom\d to zoom to the default level of @o.4`
\qzoom 20\d to set the zoom level to 20.4`

\uSEE ALSO\n
clear, client, mapper, mudletscripts
